The Cranbury School Track team competed in the annual GMC Track Meet last Friday, May 17, 2019. Jordy Paredes finished in 1st place competing in Boys Shot Put. He is the 2019 Shot Put County Champ! Akshay Patel finished 4th place in the Mile and Matthew Frenia finished 6th in the High Jump. There were many other personal best performances that day, and Mrs. Stanzione, Se√±ora Rodriguez, Mr. Stinson, and Mr. Gilligan are very proud of all the athletes who competed against a total of over 600 athletes in the county!

This season Akshay Patel broke the long-standing Cranbury School mile run record with an impressive 5 minutes and 10 second performance.

Isabella Ospina Posada also broke a long-standing Cranbury School record in the Girls 6 pound Shot Put. She threw an impressive 30 feet 8 ¬Ω inches.

Congratulations to all of our track athletes on a wonderful season!
